# UI Test Account Pool
#
# Used by gitlab_issue_campaign_dispatcher to allocate distinct test accounts
# per concurrent subagent. The pool is divided into exactly
# max_concurrent_subagents per-IID slots; per-IID slot sizes are derived
# automatically as floor(pool_size / max_concurrent_subagents) with the
# integer remainder front-loaded onto the first slots (e.g. pool=40, max=3
# → slot sizes 14,13,13). The system under test logs out an account when
# the same credentials log in twice, so concurrent subagents AND concurrent
# robot executions MUST use different accounts.
#
# This pool MUST contain at least max_concurrent_subagents entries (each
# in-flight subagent must hold ≥ 1 distinct credential) — otherwise the
# dispatcher aborts the tick (No-Fallback Policy: never share an account
# between two in-flight runs). For the slot sizes to actually cover every
# robot file an issue runs concurrently, size the pool to roughly
# max_concurrent_subagents * (max robot files per issue).
#
# Format: one account per line, "username:password". Lines starting with #
# and blank lines are ignored. Trailing whitespace is trimmed.
#
# Edited at deployment time, like gitlab.env. Trigger inputs do not override
# this file. Read by scripts/load_ui_accounts.sh.

